Environment: Next.js 15 App Router web app (rp.meavo.app). NOT Google Apps Script.

## Stack

- Next.js 15 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind
- Prisma via `@meavo/db` (shared Neon Postgres — system of record)
- NextAuth v5 (Google) + gateway `ToolCardAccess` for `RP_TOOL_CARD_ID`
- `@vercel/blob` for RP photos; `pdf-lib` for Stefan panel PDF export
- `googleapis` service account → async write-only backup to Rep.Parts26 sheet
- Vercel Cron jobs under `/api/cron/*` (see `vercel.json`)
- `@meavo/navigation` shared header

## Do NOT

- Use ES module `import`/`export` in files that must run in GAS (only `legacy-gas/` is GAS)
- Run `npm run db:push` or edit Prisma schema in this repo — schema lives in **meavo-db**
- Deploy or treat `legacy-gas/` as the live app after production cutover
- Import `@/lib/auth` (Prisma) from `middleware.ts` — use `@/lib/auth.config` only (edge-safe)

## Code layout

| Area | Path |
|------|------|
| Pages (App Router) | `src/app/(app)/` |
| Server Actions | `src/app/actions/` |
| API routes | `src/app/api/` |
| Business logic | `src/lib/domain/` |
| Sheet/Slack integrations | `src/lib/integrations/` |
| Reference data (catalogue, address book) | `src/lib/reference-data/` |
| Dashboard UI | `src/components/dashboard/` |
| Logger wizards | `src/components/logger/` |
| Auth & roles | `src/lib/auth.ts`, `src/lib/domain/authz.ts`, `src/lib/viewer-context.ts` |
| Sheet column indices | `src/lib/integrations/rp-sheet-columns.ts` |
| Legacy GAS reference (read-only) | `legacy-gas/` |

## Data flow

```
Browser → Server Actions / API → Neon (Prisma)
                               → Vercel Blob (photos)
                               → rp_sheet_sync_outbox → cron sheet-sync → Rep.Parts26
Crons → domain collectors → Slack / sheet / export tables
```

Every mutation that should appear in the sheet must call `enqueueSheetSync("rp"|"ip", entityId)` from `src/lib/domain/panel-orders.ts`.

## Spreadsheet backup (Rep.Parts26)

Canonical column mapping: `src/lib/integrations/rp-sheet-columns.ts` (`RP_COLUMN`, `IP_COLUMN`).

Legacy letter columns (for human reference):
- A: RP Num — D: Market — E: User ID — F: Issue Type — G: Urgency
- H: Model — I: Booth ID — J: Color — K: Part/Module (item type)
- L: Quantity — M: Part RP Code — N: Part Description — O: Clarifications — P: Notes
- Q: Client — R: Address — S: Recipient — T: Phone — U: Email
- V: Review group — W: Ship Method — X: Status — Y: Tracking
- AD (col 30): Workshop note (Бележка Цех) — AE (col 31): Order sent (Изпратена Поръчка)
- Internal Production tab: separate `IP_COLUMN` map; `orderSentAt` empty = not sent

## Auth & access

- `requireRpAccess()` in `src/lib/meavo-auth.ts` — session + `ToolCardAccess` gate
- Role routing: `src/lib/viewer-context.ts` + `src/lib/domain/authz.ts`
- Admins (`boyan@meavo.com`, `todor@meavo.com`) can simulate any `@meavo.com` user via cookie `rp_simulate_email`
- Persona matrix, statuses, and “where to change X”: see `docs/domain.md`

## Porting from GAS

When matching legacy behaviour, search `legacy-gas/WebAppLogic.js` and `legacy-gas/LoggerLogic.js` first.
Next.js port should live in `src/lib/domain/` (not in components or route handlers).

